The endpoint GET /api/v1/posts is implemented by PostController::index. It returns a paginated collection of PostResource items. The posts are retrieved via a search on the Post model (optionally filtered by the query parameter q), with a count of related comments, sorted by latest, and paginated using the limit parameter (default 20). The response is a resource collection, which in Laravel translates to a JSON object with a top-level data array of post representations, along with pagination metadata (links and meta). Each post representation likely includes fields used by the Post resource (id, title, content, posted_at, author_id, thumbnail_id, comments_count, created_at, updated_at). The 200 response is the only explicit success response for this endpoint in this controller action.

